## 🚨 Common Mistakes & Edge Cases

```python
# ❌ Mistake 1: Forgetting n=0 edge case
# When n=0, there's no cooldown → answer is just len(tasks)
if n == 0: return len(tasks)

# ❌ Mistake 2: Using idle_spots directly (can go negative)
return len(tasks) + idle_spots          # WRONG if idle_spots < 0
return len(tasks) + max(0, idle_spots)  # CORRECT

# ❌ Mistake 3: Off-by-one on chunks
chunks = max_freq      # WRONG
chunks = max_freq - 1  # CORRECT (last slot has no trailing cooldown)

# ✅ Edge Case: All tasks same type
tasks = ["A","A","A"], n = 2
# A _ _ A _ _ A → answer = 7
# chunks=2, idle=4, other tasks=0 → 3 + 4 = 7 ✅

# ✅ Edge Case: More task variety than cooldown
tasks = ["A","A","B","B","C","C"], n = 1
# A B A B C C → answer = 6 (= len(tasks), no idle)
# chunks=1, idle=1, B fills 1 → idle=0 → 6 + 0 = 6 ✅
```

